article.headline: Manhattan 59, Canisius 57
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- Darryl Crawford's jumper with 0:05 left gave Manhattan a 59-57 win over Canisius Monday. Devon Austin led the Jaspers with 13 points while Andrew Gabriel had 11 points and 12 rebounds as Manhattan (8-6, 2-2 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) snapped a three-game losing streak. Crawford, who scored just four points, turned in the game's most crucial plays; tying the game at 57-57 with 0:43 left after stealing the ball from Julius Coles, driving nearly the length of the court for the lay-up. Crawford drove the lane on the winning bucket as he wound through a slew of Canisius defenders and floated a five-footer for the game-winning points. Frank Turner led Canisius(5-9, 0-4 MAAC) with 18 points while Coles had 11 points and 4 rebounds. Manhattan shot just 33 percent -- 20 of 60 -- from the field and 15 of 28 from the foul line. Canisius was 23 of 54 from the floor and 7 for 12 from the line.
